  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Jeremiah 10:10",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Jeremiah 10:10",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "But the Lord ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Hebrew, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Jehovah, is the true God ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— A very different being from these idols. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "He is the living God ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Images are dead and senseless things; but Jehovah is life itself, and the author and fountain of life and understanding; and all creatures that live, live in and by him. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And an everlasting King ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— The absolute monarch over all creatures, their owner and ruler, having an incontestable right both to command and to dispose of them. And the counsels of his kingdom were from everlasting, and the continuance of it will be to everlasting. He is the king of eternity. The idols whom they call their kings are but of yesterday, and will soon be abolished; and the kings of the earth, that set them up to be worshipped, will themselves be in the dust shortly; but ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the Lord shall reign for ever, thy God, O Zion, unto all generations. At his wrath the earth shall tremble ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Even the strongest and stoutest of the kings of the earth, nay, the earth itself, as firmly as it is fixed, when he pleases, is made to quake, and the rocks to tremble. And the nations, though they join together to contend with him, and unite their force against him, shall be found utterly unable, not only to resist, but even to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "abide his indignation.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
