  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "10. true God—literally, \"God Jehovah is truth\"; not merely true, that is, veracious, but truth in the reality of His essence, as opposed to the \"vanity\" or emptiness which all idols are (Jer 10:3, 8, 15; 2Ch 15:3; Ps 31:5; 1Jo 5:20).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "living God—(Joh 5:26; 1Ti 6:17). He hath life in Himself which no creature has. All else \"live in Him\" (Ac 17:28). In contrast to dead idols.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "everlasting—(Ps 10:16). In contrast to the temporary existence of all other objects of worship.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
